1
00:00:03,197 --> 00:00:07,426
Poetry
On the Seabed

2
00:00:11,816 --> 00:00:14,083
We are at the bottom of a deep sea

3
00:00:16,211 --> 00:00:18,487
We are at the bottom of a deep sea

4
00:00:20,294 --> 00:00:23,560
A desert of words extends from directly below

5
00:00:24,663 --> 00:00:27,994
While waves of expression surfaced far above

6
00:00:29,295 --> 00:00:31,448
We can’t breathe freely

7
00:00:31,473 --> 00:00:33,227
We can’t even move our mouths

8
00:00:33,665 --> 00:00:35,955
We are at the bottom of a deep sea

9
00:00:37,988 --> 00:00:39,888
Whatever was available, was enough

10
00:00:39,913 --> 00:00:41,675
The desire to express oneself has no bounds

11
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,682
We are at the bottom of a deep sea

12
00:00:43,707 --> 00:00:45,406
At the bottom of an even deeper sea

13
00:00:45,431 --> 00:00:48,851
Floating, with a body seemingly crushed by the water pressure

14
00:00:48,876 --> 00:00:52,145
Floating, trying to reach for the moonlight on the water

15
00:00:52,306 --> 00:00:55,491
We are whales
At the bottom of an even deeper sea

16
00:00:55,516 --> 00:00:58,708
We are whales
Swallowing the krill of words

17
00:00:58,733 --> 00:01:02,730
While drawing and swimming deep in the sea of imagination

18
00:01:03,683 --> 00:01:04,963
Always

19
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:07,747
Looking for something that’s missing

20
00:01:07,772 --> 00:01:08,869
March 31st,

21
00:01:08,894 --> 00:01:10,203
Tokyo Garden Theatre

22
00:01:10,228 --> 00:01:11,392
We are Yorushika.

23
00:01:19,781 --> 00:01:24,994
｢Evening Calm, Some Place, Fireworks｣
♪～Yuunagi, Bou, Hana Madoi
Elma

24
00:01:39,573 --> 00:01:47,694
Before the seasons turned to summer,
I wrote about the fireworks in my heart

25
00:01:47,737 --> 00:01:56,551
The night is about to fall,
and the day after tomorrow is all that I see

26
00:01:56,576 --> 00:01:58,884
I’ll say it one more time

27
00:01:58,909 --> 00:02:01,324
I’ll recall that one August day

28
00:02:01,349 --> 00:02:05,199
They’re the only things I can never speak enough of

29
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,438
The two measures ring out from my guitar

30
00:02:07,463 --> 00:02:09,974
This song is 380 characters long

31
00:02:09,999 --> 00:02:11,729
I wrote rock and roll songs

32
00:02:11,754 --> 00:02:13,663
And only sang of that summer

33
00:02:13,688 --> 00:02:17,835
“Goodbye” alone is not enough

34
00:02:18,127 --> 00:02:22,461
I want to sing of glowing red days to you

35
00:02:22,486 --> 00:02:27,094
Just remembering will never be enough

36
00:02:27,119 --> 00:02:34,991
I wait for a summer with swimming flowers,
and you turn into words

37
00:02:47,116 --> 00:02:55,202
I wrote of the fireworks in that summer
so I wouldn’t forget

38
00:02:55,773 --> 00:03:03,210
The us in my memories are like ghosts you can’t see anytime but at night

39
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:06,637
There’s nothing good left

40
00:03:06,662 --> 00:03:08,848
This world was difficult for me to understand

41
00:03:08,873 --> 00:03:11,681
It’s just full of things you never taught me

42
00:03:13,442 --> 00:03:15,187
We played piano in that hall

43
00:03:15,212 --> 00:03:17,109
That cafe doesn’t exist anymore

44
00:03:17,134 --> 00:03:19,358
I want to kill the two we talked so badly about

45
00:03:19,383 --> 00:03:21,563
If you were here, you’d definitely laugh at that

46
00:03:21,588 --> 00:03:24,919
How things are now still isn’t enough

47
00:03:25,985 --> 00:03:30,168
I want us to be lost in a breeze obfuscated by flowers

48
00:03:30,193 --> 00:03:34,637
The mere act of remembering is painful

49
00:03:34,662 --> 00:03:39,221
I dream that summer will come

50
00:03:39,246 --> 00:03:43,256
And with that, a hole opened up in my heart

51
00:04:00,845 --> 00:04:05,104
Singing songs alone won’t be enough

52
00:04:05,129 --> 00:04:09,359
I want to sing of glowing red days to you

53
00:04:09,384 --> 00:04:14,026
I want to know what a beautiful night is like

54
00:04:14,051 --> 00:04:18,159
I wait for a summer of fireworks

55
00:04:18,184 --> 00:04:21,800
I am illuminated by the moonlight

56
00:04:43,701 --> 00:04:46,236
｢August, That Place, Moonlight｣
♪～Hachigatsu, Bou, Tsukiakari
That’s Why I Gave Up On Music

57
00:04:46,268 --> 00:04:47,609
I don’t need anything

58
00:05:09,019 --> 00:05:13,398
My heart became irritated; as I walked, it got hard to breathe

59
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:16,662
When I first ran away from my part-time job

60
00:05:17,346 --> 00:05:21,656
I didn’t care anymore about music or life or anything

61
00:05:22,023 --> 00:05:24,681
The number of things that annoyed me just kept increasing

62
00:05:26,514 --> 00:05:30,280
On that August day, in that place, there was moonlight, I was flying on my bike

63
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:35,187
The elevated bridge at Higashifushimi, Kodaira, Fujimidoori and the shopping area

64
00:05:35,212 --> 00:05:39,444
The night wind tickled my nose, and the pain in my heart wasn’t real–

65
00:05:39,469 --> 00:05:42,658
I understood that; I pretended to understand that

66
00:05:45,525 --> 00:05:47,971
I’m the worst, I’m the worst

67
00:05:47,996 --> 00:05:50,113
Everything about me is the worst

68
00:05:50,138 --> 00:05:52,187
I wanted something concrete to remember you by

69
00:05:52,212 --> 00:05:54,383
I don’t want to let you become just a memory!

70
00:05:54,408 --> 00:05:56,387
I’m the worst, I’m the worst

71
00:05:56,412 --> 00:05:58,754
There’s no point to just feeling good

72
00:05:58,779 --> 00:06:02,079
Because these lyrics, too, are the worst

73
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:08,276
If my life could end at twenty-seven, rock and roll saved me

74
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:12,160
By saying “Stop thinking so much! You’ll die anyway”

75
00:06:12,238 --> 00:06:14,849
I don’t need anything, even you

76
00:06:36,398 --> 00:06:38,447
My heart became irritated

77
00:06:38,472 --> 00:06:40,649
I laughed until my throat went dry

78
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:44,067
The first time I sold my heart

79
00:06:44,598 --> 00:06:48,968
I didn’t care anymore if it was pride or heart disease

80
00:06:49,085 --> 00:06:52,351
I bowed my head even to people that annoyed me

81
00:06:53,906 --> 00:06:57,243
On that August day, in that place, I strode through the scenery of the past

82
00:06:58,196 --> 00:07:02,489
The street vendors of Stockholm, Kiruna, the cobbled streets of Gamla Stan

83
00:07:02,514 --> 00:07:04,293
You were the only thing shut away inside my heart

84
00:07:04,318 --> 00:07:06,652
Even the blue of the sky is just my imagination

85
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:09,846
I was smiling; my face just stayed that way

86
00:07:12,847 --> 00:07:17,232
I’m the worst, I’m too arrogant; you’re as greedy as anyone else

87
00:07:17,257 --> 00:07:21,576
There’s no point in dramatic songs or loves, it just makes you look like a fool

88
00:07:21,601 --> 00:07:23,957
I knew, I knew

89
00:07:24,008 --> 00:07:26,177
Your life was your own

90
00:07:26,202 --> 00:07:29,624
However much I shouted “It’s the worst”

91
00:07:30,752 --> 00:07:32,511
That’s right, of course that’s right

92
00:07:32,536 --> 00:07:35,411
Rock ‘n’ roll flows through the world beyond

93
00:07:35,436 --> 00:07:36,878
While hymns and stuff aren’t that popular

94
00:07:36,903 --> 00:07:39,466
Because there’s no god

95
00:07:39,491 --> 00:07:47,003
I don’t know anything about sins or mistakes or crimes or suicide or wars or minorities

96
00:08:07,431 --> 00:08:11,639
It’s the worst, it’s the worst; to leave was arrogance

97
00:08:11,664 --> 00:08:14,214
I want to agree with you on everything

98
00:08:14,239 --> 00:08:16,302
But that would be deceiving you, Elma

99
00:08:16,327 --> 00:08:20,709
It’s the worst, it’s the worst; I can’t help this affection

100
00:08:20,734 --> 00:08:24,304
I want to mourn myself in the dramatic night

101
00:08:24,918 --> 00:08:29,122
It’s the worst, it’s the worst; these words are just redundant

102
00:08:29,147 --> 00:08:31,406
Your life is moonlight

103
00:08:31,431 --> 00:08:33,714
I could never say it was commonplace

104
00:08:33,739 --> 00:08:38,145
It’s the worst, it’s the worst; I can’t help being laughed at

105
00:08:38,170 --> 00:08:42,136
These lyrics that sound nice but mean nothing are the worst

106
00:08:42,779 --> 00:08:47,495
If my life could end at twenty-seven, rock and roll saved me

107
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:51,467
By saying “Stop thinking so much! You’ll die anyway”

108
00:08:51,524 --> 00:09:04,222
The present, love, the past, dreams, memories,
humming, light-colored eyes, night mist,

109
00:09:04,247 --> 00:09:10,489
Tenderness, pain, flowers, melancholy, that summer, this song,

110
00:09:10,514 --> 00:09:16,379
Hypocrisy, the night wind, lies, you, myself, the blue sky–I don’t need any of them

111
00:09:28,172 --> 00:09:33,665
Poetry
In Sekimachi

112
00:09:42,923 --> 00:09:44,764
I hated boring things

113
00:09:44,789 --> 00:09:46,577
That's why I hate myself

114
00:09:46,602 --> 00:09:50,284
I'm gradually getting used to living in Sekimachi

115
00:09:50,309 --> 00:09:52,137
But I can't get used to a life without you

116
00:09:52,162 --> 00:09:53,926
I can't even afford to buy flowers

117
00:09:53,951 --> 00:09:57,684
Frankly, I'm tired of the part-time work that I do for a living

118
00:09:57,709 --> 00:09:59,478
Reality is a swamp

119
00:09:59,503 --> 00:10:01,345
I'd live on music alone if I could

120
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:05,010
But it seems I'm missing something

121
00:10:05,035 --> 00:10:06,889
I was watching the sunset

122
00:10:06,914 --> 00:10:08,742
I've been walking for a while

123
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:10,556
Fujimi-dori is a shopping district

124
00:10:10,581 --> 00:10:12,419
The rotary in front of the station, a madder red

125
00:10:12,444 --> 00:10:16,112
On my way back from my part-time work, I heard a song

126
00:10:16,137 --> 00:10:17,965
In my head, it resounded

127
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:20,684
The piano you played, resounded

128
00:10:34,464 --> 00:10:38,250
If I only had a single year left to live

129
00:10:38,275 --> 00:10:40,144
What would I do now

130
00:10:40,169 --> 00:10:42,064
The value of one's life is in the way it ends

131
00:10:42,089 --> 00:10:45,330
If that was the case, then I'd like to preserve the meaning of my birth

132
00:10:45,355 --> 00:10:46,964
But I want something special

133
00:10:46,989 --> 00:10:49,351
There's nothing more boring than a novel with a sloppy ending

134
00:10:49,376 --> 00:10:54,231
That's it.
I'll turn my life into a work of art

135
00:10:54,256 --> 00:10:56,724
Elma, I'll make something
I can leave behind for you

136
00:10:56,749 --> 00:10:58,431
Somewhere in a faraway land

137
00:10:58,456 --> 00:10:59,858
In the places where I traveled

138
00:10:59,883 --> 00:11:01,098
I'll write poems

139
00:11:01,125 --> 00:11:04,232
And I'll send you back those letters and poems

140
00:11:04,258 --> 00:11:05,805
This is the year

141
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:08,125
This one year is my entire life

142
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:11,471
I want to create a work of art with my life

143
00:11:11,496 --> 00:11:13,364
I want to draw something that I can leave behind for you

144
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:16,100
I've already decided on the title of the piece

145
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,809
<i>"That's Why I Gave Up On Music"</i>

146
00:11:18,854 --> 00:11:20,667
I was watching the sunset

147
00:11:20,706 --> 00:11:22,601
I've been walking for a while

148
00:11:22,626 --> 00:11:24,441
Fujimi-dori is a shopping district

149
00:11:24,466 --> 00:11:26,350
The rotary in front of the station, a madder red

150
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:29,921
On my way back from my part-time work, I heard a song

151
00:11:29,948 --> 00:11:31,764
In my head, it resounded

152
00:11:31,789 --> 00:11:34,696
The piano you played, resounded

153
00:11:45,949 --> 00:11:48,952
｢Deep Indigo｣
♪～Ai Nijou
That’s Why I Gave Up On Music

154
00:11:48,977 --> 00:11:57,416
The scenery doesn’t change; on a faded afternoon
I’m lying in the deep indigo beneath the overpass

155
00:11:58,166 --> 00:12:02,495
I hear a single clap for my blank-page life

156
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:08,132
I was singing about my own emptiness today, as usual

157
00:12:25,857 --> 00:12:27,638
So things wouldn’t change,

158
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:33,321
I wrote a story starring you in my notebook

159
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:39,146
My gas and water being cut off, society, and the news are all someone else’s problem

160
00:12:39,171 --> 00:12:42,803
Look, my life is like ink

161
00:12:42,828 --> 00:12:55,059
The dream I had when I was young gets closer to its expiration date as I get older

162
00:12:55,084 --> 00:12:59,199
Though I just, I just look up at the clouds

163
00:12:59,224 --> 00:13:04,092
As usual, they flow through my field of vision

164
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:08,582
In the distant night sky I looked up at, flowers swam

165
00:13:08,607 --> 00:13:12,661
So many that it could be mistaken for spring

166
00:13:12,686 --> 00:13:17,025
As if I’d just lost sight of you

167
00:13:34,161 --> 00:13:37,061
I looked down so I wouldn’t trip

168
00:13:37,086 --> 00:13:42,358
Life is made of nothing but compromises

169
00:13:43,561 --> 00:13:47,849
I don’t believe in hearts or fate or love songs or life

170
00:13:47,874 --> 00:13:51,332
After all, if you can’t sell something it has no value

171
00:13:51,357 --> 00:14:03,613
I intentionally discarded the present I dreamed of,
and now I’m lying here waiting for its expiration date

172
00:14:03,638 --> 00:14:08,255
Behind my eyelids, I just, I just saw

173
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:12,624
An imagined, distant vision of you

174
00:14:12,649 --> 00:14:17,428
In my notebook, flowers swim in the corner of a faded night

175
00:14:17,453 --> 00:14:21,161
One more is in my eye

176
00:14:21,862 --> 00:14:24,624
Life is just one compromise after another

177
00:14:24,649 --> 00:14:26,740
I learned that pretty fast

178
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:27,887
Elma,

179
00:14:27,912 --> 00:14:29,324
it’s you

180
00:14:29,349 --> 00:14:31,878
You alone are my music

181
00:14:31,903 --> 00:14:34,194
There are only eighty more characters in this song

182
00:14:34,219 --> 00:14:41,077
Because maybe the only value of a life is in the way it ends

183
00:14:44,838 --> 00:14:48,994
I just, I just picture you

184
00:14:49,019 --> 00:14:53,861
As even the indigo filling my vision is blurred

185
00:14:53,886 --> 00:14:58,201
In the distant sky I looked up at, flowers swam

186
00:14:58,226 --> 00:15:02,951
Deep indigo covers my eyes

187
00:15:03,008 --> 00:15:06,471
It’s just, it’s just…

188
00:15:12,038 --> 00:15:18,167
In the distant sky I looked up at, you are cooling off

189
00:15:21,336 --> 00:15:24,786
As if you were just swimming in the night

190
00:16:02,319 --> 00:16:05,626
｢Dance of God｣
♪～Kamisama no Dance
Elma

191
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:25,814
To forget is horrible right?

192
00:16:25,839 --> 00:16:28,520
Will it turn into happiness?

193
00:16:28,545 --> 00:16:31,129
Something devoid of colour bloomed

194
00:16:31,154 --> 00:16:33,451
It bloomed in that summer without you

195
00:16:33,476 --> 00:16:36,358
Not wanting people to laugh at me

196
00:16:36,383 --> 00:16:38,886
I look at the ground as to scare them off

197
00:16:38,953 --> 00:16:43,477
Can something more important than my heart even exist?

198
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:46,450
A madder red chased the ever bright evening

199
00:16:46,475 --> 00:16:48,479
Neglecting to dye you

200
00:16:48,542 --> 00:16:52,419
Pass by me so that you can’t see me

201
00:16:54,169 --> 00:16:55,803
But please don’t go

202
00:16:56,456 --> 00:16:59,512
We who know not the face of god

203
00:16:59,538 --> 00:17:01,830
Are able to go anywhere

204
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:04,746
Hey, we’re ugly to the core

205
00:17:04,771 --> 00:17:07,488
But the world belongs to us

206
00:17:07,513 --> 00:17:09,978
It’s fine if it’s just through music right?

207
00:17:10,003 --> 00:17:12,513
We don’t have to walk in step with the rest

208
00:17:12,538 --> 00:17:15,612
Weren’t you the one who taught me that?

209
00:17:16,945 --> 00:17:20,299
It doesn’t matter to me, let’s go some place far away right now

210
00:17:20,324 --> 00:17:22,899
In a place unbeknownst to anyone,

211
00:17:24,393 --> 00:17:26,835
we’ll look for the moonlight.

212
00:17:36,191 --> 00:17:38,642
“Flowers without a name are pretty” and all that jazz

213
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:41,158
Doesn’t really matter to me

214
00:17:41,183 --> 00:17:43,764
But that phrase of yours is rubbing off on me

215
00:17:43,789 --> 00:17:46,433
Right below my throat is where you exist

216
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:51,328
Only when you’ve thrown away my words,
my life, my everything, can music be made

217
00:17:51,353 --> 00:17:56,175
How can you not understand what it costs?

218
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,081
A madder red chased the ever bright evening

219
00:17:59,106 --> 00:18:01,347
Neglecting to dye me

220
00:18:01,372 --> 00:18:04,595
One day, time will overtake everything

221
00:18:06,863 --> 00:18:09,127
But don’t disappear

222
00:18:09,152 --> 00:18:12,183
We, who know not the face of the gods

223
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:14,450
Want the whole world

224
00:18:14,475 --> 00:18:20,270
Hey, give me your all your memories, you’re ugly to the core

225
00:18:20,295 --> 00:18:22,560
If this world’s values aren’t set

226
00:18:22,585 --> 00:18:25,210
Then it’s okay to hurt each other, right?

227
00:18:25,235 --> 00:18:28,488
Weren’t you the one who didn’t teach me that?

228
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:33,025
It doesn’t matter to me, let’s go to some place far away right now

229
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:35,577
In a place no one is looking at,

230
00:18:37,035 --> 00:18:39,621
we’ll do our best imitation of living.

231
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:44,777
Dancing with ugly faces

232
00:19:01,788 --> 00:19:03,665
While our chests ache

233
00:19:03,690 --> 00:19:06,794
The gods, who know not our faces

234
00:19:06,819 --> 00:19:08,894
Are able to go anywhere

235
00:19:08,919 --> 00:19:14,146
Hey, if you say that words make up the world, then the world is ours

236
00:19:14,313 --> 00:19:16,980
To forget is horrible right?

237
00:19:17,005 --> 00:19:19,680
Will we be able to become happy that way?

238
00:19:19,705 --> 00:19:22,896
Aren’t you the one who made me think this way?

239
00:19:24,028 --> 00:19:30,385
That may be so, but regardless I’ll go some where far away right now

240
00:19:31,322 --> 00:19:34,985
And look for moonlight in a place unbeknownst to anyone

241
00:20:21,865 --> 00:20:24,991
｢False Night｣
♪～Yoru Magai
That’s Why I Gave Up On Music

242
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:52,455
Who cares about singing faithfully

243
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:57,377
I want to live taking it easier than other people,
I don’t want to work hard

244
00:20:57,825 --> 00:21:03,113
Walking along with my head down, not realizing how blue the sky is

245
00:21:03,138 --> 00:21:06,888
I’m stuck gazing only at your picture

246
00:21:07,711 --> 00:21:13,610
My hollow heart set out for a stroll in the sunset town

247
00:21:13,635 --> 00:21:22,469
The part of it that’s a lie slowly and heavily growing more taut than the barrel of a gun

248
00:21:25,942 --> 00:21:28,571
Each life is a machine gun,

