00:45:48,917 --> 00:45:51,494
That’s just how it is

506
00:45:59,878 --> 00:46:01,890
Today, I hallucinated

507
00:46:01,915 --> 00:46:04,228
That I was alive

508
00:46:04,636 --> 00:46:06,711
I’d be fine if it was just in my delusions

509
00:46:06,736 --> 00:46:09,690
I wish you could live on for me

510
00:46:09,715 --> 00:46:11,666
I write only of sad-like songs

511
00:46:11,691 --> 00:46:14,232
With emerald green trailing your cheeks

512
00:46:14,257 --> 00:46:17,147
I actually knew everything all along

513
00:46:18,369 --> 00:46:22,858
That it was the end of summer

514
00:46:23,243 --> 00:46:27,681
Reading the clouds that passed above

515
00:46:28,033 --> 00:46:36,925
The town I walk in where I have my head held high is in my memories

516
00:46:37,298 --> 00:46:42,018
I move to eat your words

517
00:46:42,102 --> 00:46:46,774
What can you see in my mouth?

518
00:46:46,876 --> 00:46:51,058
Even now, these eyes are asleep

519
00:46:51,083 --> 00:46:56,133
I was just looking at you without seeing anything

520
00:46:56,158 --> 00:46:58,974
So that I could wander around

521
00:47:18,098 --> 00:47:22,730
You’re there in front of that hill

522
00:47:22,755 --> 00:47:27,652
What can you see from your side?

523
00:47:27,677 --> 00:47:31,840
Only words reach my mouth

524
00:47:31,865 --> 00:47:36,606
I existed without knowing anything

525
00:47:36,631 --> 00:47:39,732
That’s all there is

526
00:47:42,061 --> 00:47:44,861
Even now, Amy

527
00:48:25,075 --> 00:48:28,336
｢A Hole Opened Up in My Heart｣
♪～Kokoro ni Ana ga Aita
Elma

528
00:48:54,204 --> 00:48:57,402
A small hole opened up

529
00:48:59,291 --> 00:49:03,135
Right in the middle of my chest

530
00:49:04,133 --> 00:49:07,135
A night-imitating twilight

531
00:49:08,956 --> 00:49:11,691
Painted the town

532
00:49:14,244 --> 00:49:16,606
I want to forget

533
00:49:16,631 --> 00:49:18,770
I want to forget

534
00:49:19,052 --> 00:49:26,546
But in the blue sky that buries my mind that wants to forget, I only see you

535
00:49:26,571 --> 00:49:29,104
That’s why a hole opened up in my heart

536
00:49:29,129 --> 00:49:31,654
My heartbeat pounded as if to fill it in

537
00:49:31,679 --> 00:49:33,121
When I opened my mouth to talk to you

538
00:49:33,146 --> 00:49:36,384
What came out was mostly excuses

539
00:49:36,409 --> 00:49:38,842
That’s why a hole opened up in my heart

540
00:49:38,867 --> 00:49:41,159
I thought only the falling rain was warm

541
00:49:41,184 --> 00:49:44,721
I’m fixing, fixing, fixing

542
00:49:44,746 --> 00:49:49,135
My faceless self alone

543
00:50:07,688 --> 00:50:11,838
It’s like sleeping in a forest

544
00:50:12,511 --> 00:50:17,060
where a hole has gradually opened in the light coming through the leaves

545
00:50:17,370 --> 00:50:20,734
Deep like the bottom of the sea

546
00:50:22,260 --> 00:50:25,096
Deep, like sleeping still more

547
00:50:26,246 --> 00:50:28,138
deep,

548
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:32,171
deep

549
00:50:32,196 --> 00:50:39,623
Until moonlight is seen in the depths of eyes covered up by the deep darkness of night

550
00:50:39,648 --> 00:50:42,331
I opened up a hole in your heart

551
00:50:42,356 --> 00:50:44,715
What does music matter, anyway?

552
00:50:44,740 --> 00:50:46,531
Just open your mouth

553
00:50:46,556 --> 00:50:49,681
If you stay silent, you’ll never get the things you deserve

554
00:50:49,706 --> 00:50:51,933
There are so many things I want to forget

555
00:50:51,958 --> 00:50:54,300
Only resignation comes out of my mouth

556
00:50:54,325 --> 00:50:57,911
Stumbling, stumbling, falling,

557
00:50:57,936 --> 00:51:02,676
feeling only the cold ground

558
00:51:20,383 --> 00:51:25,217
I want to write about my life, which I wanted to make into your life

559
00:51:25,242 --> 00:51:27,500
It’s because of the songs you left behind

560
00:51:27,525 --> 00:51:29,983
It’s all music’s fault

561
00:51:30,008 --> 00:51:32,225
I imitated the way you spoke

562
00:51:32,250 --> 00:51:34,458
I copied the way you lived

563
00:51:34,483 --> 00:51:39,190
But though I tried to erase myself so that nothing of me would remain

564
00:51:39,215 --> 00:51:41,419
It remains still

565
00:51:43,476 --> 00:51:46,125
I clung to your words

566
00:51:46,150 --> 00:51:48,575
Which nestled in the hole in my heart

567
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:50,275
But it’s different now

568
00:51:50,300 --> 00:51:53,309
I don’t ever want to hear “goodbye”

569
00:51:53,334 --> 00:51:55,775
There are so many things I want to forget

570
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:58,142
From now on, only I will grow older

571
00:51:58,167 --> 00:52:01,095
Growing colder, growing colder

572
00:52:05,273 --> 00:52:07,823
A hole opened up in my heart

573
00:52:07,848 --> 00:52:10,173
Your words opened a hole in my heart

574
00:52:10,198 --> 00:52:11,790
I understand now

575
00:52:11,815 --> 00:52:15,073
“You alone are my music,” Amy

576
00:52:15,098 --> 00:52:17,323
That’s why a hole opened up in my heart

577
00:52:17,348 --> 00:52:19,940
You were nestled on the other side of it

578
00:52:19,965 --> 00:52:23,564
It will never go back to the way it was

579
00:52:23,589 --> 00:52:27,983
It’s just a hole that’s spreading, spreading, spreading

580
00:52:30,724 --> 00:52:35,338
Just me, with a hole in my heart

581
00:54:35,301 --> 00:54:38,340
｢Parade｣
♪～Parade
That’s Why I Gave Up On Music

582
00:54:52,213 --> 00:54:56,262
Inside my body,

583
00:54:56,581 --> 00:55:00,640
right below my throat,

584
00:55:00,949 --> 00:55:06,529
if there’s a heart then you

585
00:55:06,942 --> 00:55:11,717
must be there

586
00:55:27,450 --> 00:55:35,271
I’ve known for a long time

587
00:55:36,114 --> 00:55:44,573
That as I got older I would even forget your face

588
00:55:44,598 --> 00:56:02,227
Because I want to know the moment that words are able to form inside my body, in my throat

589
00:56:02,252 --> 00:56:09,563
If the dawn comes like this…

590
00:56:09,937 --> 00:56:13,935
I hope that my memories don’t dry out

591
00:56:14,260 --> 00:56:18,401
I hope that I don’t lose this song

592
00:56:18,651 --> 00:56:26,401
Don’t forget, for just a little longer,

593
00:56:27,452 --> 00:56:32,268
The lonely parade

594
00:56:48,057 --> 00:56:55,814
I’ve thought for a long time that

595
00:56:56,397 --> 00:57:05,745
Gods might reside in your fingertips

596
00:57:05,770 --> 00:57:13,681
Since before today, before yesterday,

597
00:57:14,161 --> 00:57:19,969
since a long, long time past

598
00:57:22,351 --> 00:57:27,772
I’ve known that

599
00:57:57,933 --> 00:58:06,152
Inside my body, right below my throat

600
00:58:06,407 --> 00:58:15,197
Are the days when I’ve only been imitating your song

601
00:58:16,399 --> 00:58:20,008
I hope that I don’t forget

602
00:58:25,190 --> 00:58:30,600
The temperature of this moment in which you’re not here

603
00:58:33,899 --> 00:58:37,956
With memories that I hope won’t dry out

604
00:58:37,981 --> 00:58:42,639
With this song that I haven’t been able to forget

605
00:58:42,664 --> 00:58:49,897
Just a little bit more, for just a little longer

606
00:58:53,547 --> 00:58:58,676
I’ll make a lonely parade

607
00:59:47,884 --> 00:59:51,833
｢Seabed, Moonlight｣
♪～Kaitei, Tsukiakari
Elma

608
01:00:58,700 --> 01:01:00,700
｢Just Sorrow｣
♪～Yuu Ichijou
Elma

609
01:01:00,725 --> 01:01:04,808
I think I’m at the bottom of a river

610
01:01:06,690 --> 01:01:10,491
A single breath constricts my throat

611
01:01:12,513 --> 01:01:15,668
Watching the air escape my mouth for a few seconds,

612
01:01:15,693 --> 01:01:17,952
my feet finally touched the ground

613
01:01:17,977 --> 01:01:22,441
I felt the gentle bubbles

614
01:01:23,847 --> 01:01:26,959
For a long time

615
01:01:26,984 --> 01:01:29,876
For a long time

616
01:01:29,901 --> 01:01:35,567
For a long, long, long time now

617
01:01:35,592 --> 01:01:41,686
Just by chasing after you

618
01:01:41,711 --> 01:01:47,406
I’ve wanted to talk only about things beyond my control

619
01:01:47,988 --> 01:01:53,946
The water lilies floated along the water, transparent

620
01:01:53,971 --> 01:01:59,169
If it's only a little more certain than a mirage already, that’d be great

621
01:01:59,966 --> 01:02:02,947
I’d be fine if you did the bare minimum

622
01:02:03,291 --> 01:02:05,906
I’d be fine if it was something we aimed for

623
01:02:05,931 --> 01:02:09,747
At this rate, I’d be fine with going anywhere, so let’s run away

624
01:02:15,710 --> 01:02:19,430
I think I’m at the bottom of a river

625
01:02:21,568 --> 01:02:26,019
My wet eardrums feel ticklish

626
01:02:27,475 --> 01:02:33,241
I didn’t want to ask about hopes, the future, tomorrow, or anything really

627
01:02:33,266 --> 01:02:38,099
Those questions died quickly just by seeing the beauty of the bubbles escaping my mouth

628
01:02:38,847 --> 01:02:41,843
For a long time

629
01:02:41,868 --> 01:02:44,260
For a long time

630
01:02:44,868 --> 01:02:50,758
For a long, long, long time now

631
01:02:50,783 --> 01:02:57,479
Just by being enchanted by it

632
01:02:57,504 --> 01:03:02,548
I wanted to find something more important than my heart

633
01:03:03,239 --> 01:03:08,762
Words are cruel, above the water they seem transparent

634
01:03:08,787 --> 01:03:14,081
Hey, I’m looking for something prettier than how to act properly

635
01:03:14,639 --> 01:03:20,122
It’s fine to forget about it though, so let’s run away

636
01:03:24,689 --> 01:03:27,655
I don’t need this self of mine

637
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:30,547
I don’t need anything

638
01:03:30,572 --> 01:03:35,906
I don’t need money, or fame, or love, or recognition — nothing

639
01:03:35,931 --> 01:03:38,827
I want to go far away right now,

640
01:03:38,852 --> 01:03:42,118
Touch the outside of these memories,

641
01:03:42,143 --> 01:03:46,854
And listen to your songs once more

642
01:03:50,910 --> 01:03:53,654
For a long time

643
01:03:53,980 --> 01:03:56,579
For a long time

644
01:03:56,964 --> 01:04:02,630
For a long, long, long time now

645
01:04:02,655 --> 01:04:11,085
Just by chasing after you

646
01:04:12,691 --> 01:04:17,298
I’ve wanted to sing only about things I can’t control

647
01:04:18,191 --> 01:04:23,870
The water lilies floated along the water, looking transparent

648
01:04:23,895 --> 01:04:29,084
If it's only a little more certain than a mirage already, that’d be great

649
01:04:29,579 --> 01:04:32,793
At this rate, I’d be fine with going anywhere

650
01:04:32,818 --> 01:04:38,391
The truth is that I’ve only been wanting to leave everything behind and run away

651
01:04:39,259 --> 01:04:44,898
This life is transparent, above the water, seemingly transparent

652
01:04:44,923 --> 01:04:50,035
I’ve had enough. If it’s only a little more certain than a mirage, I’d be fine with it

653
01:04:50,982 --> 01:04:53,871
I’d be fine if you did the bare minimum

654
01:04:54,140 --> 01:04:56,908
I’d be fine if it was something we aimed for

655
01:04:56,933 --> 01:05:01,871
At this rate, I’d be fine with going anywhere, so let’s run away

656
01:05:40,410 --> 01:05:43,380
｢Nautilus｣
♪～Nautilus
Elma

657
01:05:43,405 --> 01:05:49,304
When the alarm clock rang, I finally woke up

658
01:05:49,329 --> 01:05:54,328
The flu I had yesterday doesn’t seem real anymore

659
01:05:55,321 --> 01:06:01,176
I think of going out, but, ah, the forecast says it looks like rain

660
01:06:01,201 --> 01:06:07,112
Well, I couldn’t go anyway because it’s still dark

661
01:06:07,137 --> 01:06:13,062
A dry throat, a hurting heart–

662
01:06:13,087 --> 01:06:18,594
all these human things are getting in my way

663
01:06:21,011 --> 01:06:28,877
Lift your head at the speed of the farewell

664
01:06:28,902 --> 01:06:31,547
Someday dawn will finally break

665
01:06:31,572 --> 01:06:36,975
Come on, try and open your eyes

666
01:06:37,000 --> 01:06:45,263
Because I’ve pictured your sleepy eyes so many times

667
01:06:56,702 --> 01:07:08,843
I finally decided to take an umbrella and go out anyway,
which was good, but I think I might’ve thrown away my shoes

668
01:07:08,868 --> 01:07:14,664
And it’s not like I’ve got the courage to go barefoot, so...

669
01:07:14,689 --> 01:07:20,289
I guess I don’t really care? What do I want to do?

670
01:07:20,720 --> 01:07:23,256
What should I do for dinner?

671
01:07:23,443 --> 01:07:26,578
If the rain lets up, I’ll go out

672
01:07:26,784 --> 01:07:31,923
Even though I don’t really want to see people

673
01:07:34,431 --> 01:07:42,418
At this speed I swim through today,

674
01:07:42,443 --> 01:07:45,020
And if my hand finally touches you…

675
01:07:45,045 --> 01:07:50,285
Come on, try and open your eyes

676
01:07:50,667 --> 01:07:58,158
Because I remember you and your sleepy eyes, even though I’ve forgotten them

677
01:07:59,724 --> 01:08:05,754
There you are by the hill, laughing,
“It’s been so long, hasn’t it?”

678
01:08:05,779 --> 01:08:08,287
as you bring your face close to mine

679
01:08:08,312 --> 01:08:11,501
“Let’s go together,” you say

680
01:08:11,829 --> 01:08:14,754
Under a barn in Lappland

681
01:08:14,779 --> 01:08:17,654
On the old streets of Gamla Stan

682
01:08:17,679 --> 01:08:22,412
The summer grass is getting in my way

683
01:08:25,543 --> 01:08:33,226
At this speed I swim through today,

684
01:08:33,251 --> 01:08:36,041
And if my hand finally touches you…

685
01:08:36,066 --> 01:08:41,624
Come on, open your eyes

686
01:08:41,649 --> 01:08:46,060
And see that I’ve forgotten you

687
01:08:46,497 --> 01:08:54,347
Lift your head at the speed of the farewell

688
01:08:54,372 --> 01:08:56,931
Someday dawn will finally break

689
01:08:56,956 --> 01:09:02,654
Come on, open your eyes

690
01:09:02,682 --> 01:09:10,292
And see that I’ve drawn pictures of your sleepy eyes so many times

691
01:10:02,213 --> 01:10:05,731
Poetry
Revolving Lantern

692
01:10:18,165 --> 01:10:20,449
A song resounds within my head

693
01:10:20,474 --> 01:10:22,373
There’s a melody ringing out

694
01:10:22,390 --> 01:10:26,151
My chest is in pain, I’m struggling, unable to breathe

695
01:10:26,176 --> 01:10:29,743
Beyond 0 meters above sea level, my blurred vision wavers

696
01:10:29,768 --> 01:10:36,768
The light shining through the crevices of the pier
sparkles like moonlight hitting the water’s surface

697
01:10:37,230 --> 01:10:39,435
I’m at the bottom of a deep sea

698
01:10:41,929 --> 01:10:44,390
I’m at the bottom of a deep sea

699
01:10:50,751 --> 01:10:52,126
I understand now,

700
01:10:52,151 --> 01:10:54,917
The light that I’d always been seeing

701
01:10:54,942 --> 01:10:56,268
the scenery,

702
01:10:56,293 --> 01:10:57,693
my memories,

703
01:10:57,718 --> 01:10:59,752
the rainy café terrace,

704
01:10:59,777 --> 01:11:01,978
the night-imitating twilight,

705
01:11:02,003 --> 01:11:03,527
Fujimidoori,

706
01:11:03,552 --> 01:11:07,434
my journey to find the closest place to heaven,

707
01:11:07,459 --> 01:11:08,709
the melodies,

708
01:11:08,734 --> 01:11:10,484
the music,

709
01:11:10,509 --> 01:11:14,159
this moment in time that feels like I’m having a long dream,

710
01:11:14,184 --> 01:11:16,270
the scenery of that day,

711
01:11:17,969 --> 01:11:19,959
all of it,

712
01:11:22,153 --> 01:11:24,024
What I’m looking upon - it’s a revolving lantern

713
01:11:24,049 --> 01:11:25,196
｢That’s Why I Gave Up On Music｣
♪～Dakara Boku wa Ongaku wo Yameta
That’s Why I Gave Up On Music

714
01:11:25,221 --> 01:11:27,446
I’ve thought about it, but I still don’t understand

715
01:11:27,471 --> 01:11:29,296
Under the blue sky, I waited for you

716
01:11:29,321 --> 01:11:32,638
On that breezy afternoon, my imagination escaped the confines of the day

717
01:11:32,663 --> 01:11:34,788
Hey, where do I go from here?

718
01:11:34,813 --> 01:11:37,188
No one has told me how to proceed

719
01:11:37,213 --> 01:11:41,575
I looked into your eyes and without a word I walked away

720
01:11:56,087 --> 01:11:57,937
I’ve thought about it, but I still don’t understand

721
01:11:57,962 --> 01:11:59,770
Youth is so boring

722
01:11:59,795 --> 01:12:03,374
I tried to give up piano, but I can’t break the habit of playing on my desk

723
01:12:03,399 --> 01:12:05,666
Hey, what will I do in the future?

724
01:12:05,691 --> 01:12:08,795
It shouldn’t be music, right?

725
01:12:09,319 --> 01:12:10,707
Don’t worry

726
01:12:10,856 --> 01:12:19,006
Even if I drew a single line in my heart

727
01:12:19,031 --> 01:12:21,974
No matter what I did, it wouldn’t disappear, even now, so

728
01:12:21,999 --> 01:12:26,046
Hey, I still remember

729
01:12:26,071 --> 01:12:27,388
I’m mistaken

730
01:12:27,413 --> 01:12:29,938
I don’t understand, I don’t care

731
01:12:29,963 --> 01:12:33,855
About all you humans or the truth or love or the world or pain or life

732
01:12:33,880 --> 01:12:37,690
Wanting to know what’s right or wrong is just a self-preservation instinct

733
01:12:37,715 --> 01:12:40,886
It’s your fault that I thought that

734
01:12:55,707 --> 01:12:59,538
I’ve thought about it, but I still don’t understand why I truly don’t want to get older

735
01:12:59,563 --> 01:13:03,088
Just thinking “Someday I’m going to die” makes my chest feel hollow

736
01:13:03,113 --> 01:13:04,886
“What will I do in the future?”

737
01:13:04,911 --> 01:13:07,939
When I grew up I understood

738
01:13:08,842 --> 01:13:10,290
That I’m not going to do anything at all

739
01:13:10,315 --> 01:13:20,407
How do I explain why I hate people who put on happy faces?

740
01:13:20,432 --> 01:13:27,580
It’s an inferiority complex haunting my unsatisfied mind like a ghost

741
01:13:27,605 --> 01:13:28,715
I’m not mistaken

742
01:13:28,740 --> 01:13:31,182
Hey, with all your differences, you all are human

743
01:13:31,207 --> 01:13:35,282
When you don’t have love or salvation or kindness or a foundation, it feels bad

744
01:13:35,307 --> 01:13:39,155
Feeling pain at something like a love song is a self-preservation instinct

745
01:13:39,180 --> 01:13:42,244
Do I really not care? It’s your fault

746
01:13:56,991 --> 01:13:58,991
I’ve thought about it, but I still don’t understand

747
01:13:59,016 --> 01:14:00,758
Why just living is painful

748
01:14:00,783 --> 01:14:02,675
Why you can’t make a living from something like music

749
01:14:02,700 --> 01:14:05,637
I don’t care if the lyrics or whatever are lazily done

750
01:14:07,716 --> 01:14:09,837
I don’t care about anything

751
01:14:11,619 --> 01:14:13,837
I’m probably not mistaken

752
01:14:15,856 --> 01:14:17,837
I’m sure I’m not mistaken

753
01:14:19,473 --> 01:14:21,504
I’m sure I’m not mistaken

754
01:14:32,914 --> 01:14:35,284
I’m mistaken, I understand

755
01:14:35,309 --> 01:14:36,886
I don’t care

756
01:14:36,911 --> 01:14:40,431
